 \nfn = (x) => typeof x === \"string\"\nOutput: {\"b\":\"2\",\"d\":\"4\"}\nExplanation: All keys with values that were not a string were removed. When the object keys were removed during the filtering process, any resulting empty objects were also removed.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: \nobj = [-1, [-1, -1, 5, -1, 10], -1, [-1], [-5]], \nfn = (x) => x > 0\nOutput: [[5,10]]\nExplanation: All values that were not greater than 0 were removed. When the values were removed during the filtering process, any resulting empty arrays were also removed.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Example 4:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":7,"text":"Input: \nobj = [[[[5]]]], \nfn = (x) => Array.isArray(x)\nOutput: undefined","type":"code"},{"sequence":8,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `fn` is a function that returns a boolean value\n\n- `obj` is a valid JSON object or array\n\n- `2 <= JSON.stringify(obj).length <= 10⁵`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["JavaScript"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given an object or an array `obj` and a function `fn`, return a filtered object or array `filteredObject`.\n\nFunction `deepFilter` should perform a deep filter operation on the `obj`. The deep filter operation should remove properties for which the output of the filter function `fn` is `false`, as well as any empty objects or arrays that remain after the keys have been removed.\n\nIf the deep filter operation results in an empty object or array, with no remaining properties, `deepFilter` should return `undefined` to indicate that there is no valid data left in the `filteredObject`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: \nobj = [-5, -4, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1], \nfn = (x) => x > 0\nOutput: [1]\nExplanation: All values that were not greater than 0 were removed.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: \nobj = {\"a\": 1, \"b\": \"2\", \"c\": 3, \"d\": \"4\", \"e\": 5, \"