ximum sum*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [8,7,3,5,7,2,4,9]\n\n**Output:** 16\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nWe select elements at indices 2 and 8 and `2 * 8` is a perfect square.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [8,10,3,8,1,13,7,9,4]\n\n**Output:** 20\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nWe select elements at indices 1, 4, and 9. `1 * 4`, `1 * 9`, `4 * 9` are perfect squares.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n == nums.length <= 10⁴`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-element-sum-of-a-complete-subset-of-indices/","problemName":"Maximum Element-Sum of a Complete Subset of Indices","problemNumber":2862,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **1****-indexed** array `nums`. Your task is to select a **complete subset** from `nums` where every pair of selected indices multiplied is a [perfect square,](leetcode-keyword). i. e. if you select `ai` and `aj`, `i * j` must be a perfect square.\n\nReturn the *sum* of the complete subset with the *maximum sum*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [8,7,3,5,7,2,4,9]\n\n**Output:** 16\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nWe select elements at indices 2 and 8 and `2 * 8` is a perfect square.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [8,10,3,8,1,13,7,9,4]\n\n**Output:** 20\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nWe select elements at indices 1, 4, and 9. `1 * 4`, `1 * 9`, `4 * 9` are perfect squares.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n == nums.length <= 10⁴`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Hard","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given a **1****-indexed** array `nums`. Your task is to select a **complete subset** from `nums` where every pair of selected indices multiplied is a [perfect square,](leetcode-keyword). i. e. if you select `ai` and `aj`, `i * j` must be a perfect square.\n\nReturn the *sum* of the complete subset with t