xists no other beautiful configuration with a sum of heights greater than 22.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: maxHeights = [3,2,5,5,2,3]\nOutput: 18\nExplanation: One beautiful configuration with a maximum sum is heights = [2,2,5,5,2,2]. This configuration is beautiful since:\n- 1 <= heights[i] <= maxHeights[i]\n- heights is a mountain of peak i = 2. \nNote that, for this configuration, i = 3 can also be considered a peak.\nIt can be shown that there exists no other beautiful configuration with a sum of heights greater than 18.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n == maxHeights.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= maxHeights[i] <= 10⁹`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/beautiful-towers-ii/","problemName":"Beautiful Towers II","problemNumber":2866,"problemSlug":"beautiful-towers-ii","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2866,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":17310,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2867-count-valid-paths-in-a-tree/2867-example1.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2867-example1.png","sha256":"40ed9506140279a4a4b9d38036881026aa61606c04908da2143054d3cae4c2a0"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":20408,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2867-count-valid-paths-in-a-tree/2867-example2.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/2867-example2.png","sha256":"fc0ffe4e10c2278ed076ef30f5ba8cc8029969607692126105c879df72bfc025"}],"categories":["Math","Dynamic Programming","Tree","Depth-First Search","Number Theory"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There is an undirected tree with `n` nodes labeled from `1` to `n`. You are given the integer `n` and a 2D integer array `edges` of length `n - 1`, where `edges[i] = [ui, vi]` indicates that there is an edge between nodes `ui` and `vi` in the tree.\n\nReturn *the **number of valid paths** in the tree*.\n\nA path `(a, b)` is **valid** if there exists **exactly one** prime number among the node labels in the path from `a` to `b`.\n\n**Note** that:\n\n- The path `(a, b)` is a sequence of **distinct** nodes starting with node `a` and ending with node `b` such that every two adjacent nodes in the sequence share an edge in the tree.\n\n- Path `(a, b)` and path `(b, a)` are considered the **same** and counted only **once**.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2867-count-valid-paths-in-a-tree/2867-example1.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"40ed9506140279a4a4b9d38036881026aa61606c04908da2143054d3cae4c2a0","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: n = 5, edges = [[1,2],[1,3],[2,4],[2,5]]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: The pairs with exactly one prime number on the path between them are: \n- (1, 2) since the path from 1 to 2 contains prime number 2. \n- (1, 3) since the path from 1 to 3 contains prime number 3.\n- (1, 4) since the path from 1 to 4 contains prime number 2.\n- (2, 4) since the path from 2 to 4 contains prime number 2.\nIt can be shown that there are only 4 valid paths.","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/2867-count-valid-paths-in-a-tree/2867-example2.png","sequence":4,"sha256":"fc0ffe4e10c2278ed076ef30f5ba8cc8029969607692126105c879df72bfc025","type":"image"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: n = 6, edges = [[1,2],[1,3],[2,4],[3,5],[3,6]]\nOutput: 6\nExplanation: The pairs with exactly one prime number on the path between them are: \n- (1, 2) since the path from 1 to 2 contains prime number 2.\n- (1, 3) since the path from 1 to 3 contains prime number 3.\n- (1, 4) since the path from 1 to 4 contains prime number 2.\n- (1, 6) since the path from 1 to 6 contains prime number 3.\n- (2, 4) since the path from 2 to 4 contains prime number 2.\n- (3, 6) since the path from 3 to 6 contains prime number 3.\nIt can be shown that there are only 6 valid paths.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Co